HEADWORD: Free-swimming
<hw>Free"-swim`ming</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Swimming in the open sea; -- said of certain marine
animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zoology)</fld> <def>able to swim about; not
attached to a stationary object; -- of aquatic animals.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> unattached.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>freetail</ent>⟦br⟧
